President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of North Carolina and has ordered Federal aid to assist with recovery efforts following Hurricane Dorian. The Federal funding will be available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work, facility repairs, and facility replacements in the affected counties. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for cost-sharing funding. Elizabeth Turner has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.